# QA Automation Exercises – project context

## Stack
- Playwright (JavaScript), E2E + API tests
- Page Object Model, custom fixtures

## Structure
- `tests/e2e/` — E2E: `fixtures.js` (inject page objects), `helpers/` (BasePage, data.helper), `pageObjects/`, `specs/`
- `tests/api/` — API: `helpers/` (https-helper, function-helper), `specs/`
- Config: `playwright.config.js` (BASE_URL, projects: api, e2e-chrome, e2e-firefox)

## Conventions
- E2E specs use fixtures: `require('../fixtures')` and inject `homePage`, `productsPage`, `productDetailsPage`, `cartPage` in test/beforeEach.
- Page objects extend `BasePage`; use `this.goto(path)` for navigation. Locators in constructor, actions as async methods.
- Test data: `tests/e2e/helpers/data.helper.js`. No hardcoded URLs; use BASE_URL in config.
- Tag tests: `{ tag: ['@smoke', '@regression', '@home', '@cart', '@pdp', '@api'] }`. Run with `npx playwright test --grep @smoke`.

## Commands
- `npm run test:e2e:chrome` / `test:e2e:firefox` / `test:api`
- `npm run lint` / `npm run format`

## Don't
- Use `page.waitForTimeout()` — use `expect(locator).toHaveCount()` or `waitForLoadState` / `waitFor({ state })`.
- Put assertions in afterAll; use a dedicated test or test.step() for cleanup checks.
- Duplicate cart logic in ProductsPage; cart belongs in CartPage only.
